                    "ref_id": "FIGREF0"
                }
            ],
            "section": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "The presence of inflammation in normally aerated lung regions has already been shown in patients with ARDS [3] or in patients at risk for ARDS and subsequently developing the disease [4] . Thus, although the pattern observed in this patient does not seem specific to infection from influenza A, we believe that the image conveys the message well that the virus can trigger an extremely intense inflammatory ",
